        <title>Which kicksecure security features can be implemented in non-debian distros?</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[arraybolt3]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Possible? Yes, almost certainly. A very large portion of Kicksecure’s code is likely distro-agnostic (though as a Debian derivative we do use Debianisms in some of our code and some of our code is also specific to Debian, for instance things that have to do with deb packages).</p>
